        <title>Data Management Plan</title>
        <description>-Open access practices will be employed that will help reach the goals set and meet all the objectives. Such practices include a data repository that all the participating researcher will have access to, pre-prints will be put on online platforms, results will be discussed on a weekly basis with all the research parties involved and data will be also managed in a way that all the participants could access it, e.g. data put on cloud. An online library with relevant publications from other research groups will be created and updated on a daily basis, allowing for the researchers involved with the project to be notified and get informed about ongoing research related to the SYZEFXIS project.-One of the aims of the proposed research project is to demonstrate, in a proof-of-principle experiment, enhanced stability of organic semiconductors in strong-coupled electrically-driven hybrid LED devices, with this work potentially resulting in new consumer-market applications. Patent opportunities will be exploited, as well as the best strategies for intellectual property protection will be employed. This will be achieved by close collaboration with the patent office at UCY that will consult the consortium members on the measures to be taken.</description>
